text="Pittsposium: A Workshop Celebrating the Career of Andrew Pitts"><fr:em>Pittsposium</fr:em>: A Workshop Celebrating the Career of <fr:link
href="andrewpitts.xml"
title="Andrew Pitts"
addr="andrewpitts"
type="local">Andrew Pitts</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Workshop</fr:taxon><fr:meta
name="venue"><fr:link
href="camcl.xml"
title="Cambridge Computer Laboratory"
addr="camcl"
type="local">Cambridge Computer Laboratory</fr:link></fr:meta><fr:meta
name="external">https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/events/pittsposium/</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:blockquote><fr:p><fr:link
href="andrewpitts.xml"
title="Andrew Pitts"
addr="andrewpitts"
type="local">Andrew Pitts</fr:link> is Professor of Theoretical Computer Science in the <fr:link
href="ucam.xml"
title="University of Cambridge"
addr="ucam"
type="local">University of Cambridge</fr:link>, having joined the <fr:link
href="camcl.xml"
title="Cambridge Computer Laboratory"
addr="camcl"
type="local">Computer Laboratory</fr:link> as a Lecturer in 1989. He holds a PhD in Mathematics, also from Cambridge, and is a Fellow of Darwin College. His early research interests were in applications of category theory in logic and mathematical foundations; from around 1985 onwards these turned to applications in the semantics of programming languages. His work in theoretical computer science has ranged over category theory, constructive logic, type theory, programming language semantics, and the design and implementation of metaprogramming languages. <fr:link
href="andrewpitts.xml"
title="Andrew Pitts"
addr="andrewpitts"
type="local">Prof. Pitts</fr:link> is an ACM Fellow and a recipient of the Alonzo Church Award for Outstanding Contributions to Logic and Computation.</fr:p>

  <fr:p>Through his career <fr:link
href="andrewpitts.xml"
title="Andrew Pitts"
addr="andrewpitts"
type="local">Andy</fr:link> has supervised twelve doctoral students, published research with dozens of collaborators, and inspired many more with his gentle and persuasive instruction. Always generous with fresh ideas, his far-sighted intuition and enthusiasm has guided the community in innovative research for over four decades. <fr:link
href="https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/events/pittsposium/pittsposium_bio.pdf"
type="external">A longer biography is available here.</fr:link></fr:p>

  <fr:p>We are delighted to invite the community to participate in this workshop as a celebration of <fr:link
href="andrewpitts.xml"
title="Andrew Pitts"
addr="andrewpitts"
type="local">Andy</fr:link>’s research and long career, with talks to be given by many of his students, colleagues and collaborators.</fr:p></fr:blockquote></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
